.TH CASTELLAN 1 "2026" "Castellan" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
castellan \- agentless hardening of Ubuntu and Debian servers
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B castellan
.I command
.RI [ host | target "] [" args ...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Castellan applies security hardening to Ubuntu/Debian servers over SSH, driven
by Ansible. It runs a read-only audit and an idempotent apply in a strict
anti-lockout order, with selectable profiles and an interactive setup. Nothing
is installed on the target.
.PP
Per-host configuration is stored under
.IR ~/.config/castellan/host_vars/ ;
fetched reports under
.IR ~/.config/castellan/reports/ .
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B init \fIhost\fR
Interactive setup of a new host (wizard).
.TP
.B configure \fIhost\fR
Pick the profile and individual measures (roles then a checklist).
.TP
.B list
List configured hosts, their profile and enabled measures.
.TP
.B audit \fItarget\fR [args...]
Read-only compliance audit (no changes).
.TP
.B apply \fItarget\fR [args...]
Apply hardening.
.TP
.B rollback \fItarget\fR [args...]
Restore the latest backup.
.TP
.B report \fItarget\fR
Show the latest report per host.
.PP
.I target
is any Ansible host pattern: a single host, a comma-separated list, an
inventory group, or \fBall\fR. Extra arguments are passed to
.BR ansible-playbook (1).
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
castellan init srv-01
castellan apply srv-01 --ask-pass -e hardening_profile=paranoid
castellan apply web1,web2 --only ssh,firewall
.fi
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /usr/share/castellan
Program files (playbooks, roles, library).
.TP
.I ~/.config/castellan
Per-user host configuration, keys and reports.
